===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|aloiier||assemble, join}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|alligare||bind to, tie to}}, compound of {{m|la|ad||to}} + {{m|la|ligare||to bind}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To [[mix]] or combine; often used of metals.
# To [[reduce]] the [[purity]] of by [[mixing]] with a [[less]] [[valuable]] [[substance]].
#: ''to '''alloy''' gold with silver or copper, or silver with copper''
# {{lb|en|figurative}} To [[impair]] or [[debase]] by mixture.
#: ''to '''alloy''' pleasure with misfortunes''

